1 AN ACT relating to real estate license reciprocity.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 324.115 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Except as provided in subsection (2) of this section, every broker licensed under
5 KRS 324.045 shall maintain a definite place of business in this state.
6 (2) A broker who is a nonresident shall not be required to maintain an active place of
7 business in this state if:
8 (a) He or she maintains a business place in the state of original licensure;
9 (b) The state of original licensure[, in accordance with its reciprocity agreement
10 with the commission,] does not require Kentucky licensees holding licenses in
11 that state to maintain an office in that state; and
12 (c) Paragraphs (a) and (b) of this subsection do not conflict with a reciprocity
13 agreement[the commission's agreement of reciprocity] with the state of
14 original licensure.
15 Section 2. KRS 324.141 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) (a) An individual who holds an active real estate license issued by another
17 jurisdiction within the United States that does not have a valid mutual
18 recognition, reciprocity, or cooperation agreement with the commission may
19 apply for a Kentucky license by[ first]:
20 1. Completing the application forms;
21 2. Passing only the state law portion of the licensing examination;[ and]
22 3. For a sales associate license, submitting proof of completion of a forty
23 (40) classroom hour reciprocal Kentucky state license law course; and
24 4. For a broker license, submitting proof of completion of a forty (40)
25 classroom hour reciprocal Kentucky state license law course and a
26 forty-eight (48) classroom hour broker management course[Fulfilling
27 all other pre-license qualifications as outlined in this chapter].
