1 (b) The commission shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance
2 with KRS Chapter 13A to establish the procedures for implementing
3 paragraph (a) of this subsection.
4 (2) All individuals who have held a real estate license in another jurisdiction, whether
5 the license is currently active or canceled, shall be required to furnish, as part of his
6 or her application for a Kentucky license, a certification of good standing, issued by
7 the jurisdiction. The document shall include the individual's license history and any
8 disciplinary information available from that jurisdiction.
9 (3) Every nonresident applicant shall file an irrevocable consent stating that legal
10 actions may be commenced against the applicant in the proper court of any county
11 of this state in which a cause of action may arise in which the plaintiff may reside,
12 by the service of any process or pleading authorized by the laws of this state on the
13 commission, the consent stipulating and agreeing that service of process or
14 pleadings on the commission shall be taken and held in all courts to be as valid and
15 binding as if service had been made upon the applicant in the State of Kentucky.
16 Any process or pleadings served upon the commission shall be by duplicate copies,
17 one (1) of which shall be filed in the office of the commission and the other
18 immediately forwarded by certified mail, return receipt requested, to the main
19 office of the applicant against which the process or pleadings are directed.
20 (4) The education, examination, and application requirements under subsection
21 (1)(a) of this section shall apply to any applicant from another jurisdiction that
22 does not have a valid mutual recognition, reciprocity, or cooperation agreement
23 with the commission. Any education requirements approved by the commission
24 pursuant to an existing mutual recognition, reciprocity, or cooperation agreement
25 between the jurisdiction from which the applicant is seeking reciprocity and the
26 commission shall be sufficient to satisfy the education requirements under
27 subsection (1)(a) of this section through the expiration of the agreement. The
